<TITLE> India's Ashok Leyland, Siemens VDO in joint venture </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MUMBAI, July 16 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Ashok Leyland Ltd, India's second-biggest bus and truck maker, said on Monday it had signed a joint venture deal with components supplier Siemens VDO Automotive AG. The equal joint venture will design, develop and adapt infotronics products and services for the transportation sector in India and overseas, Leyland said in a statement. It did not disclose financial detail
